2025-07-25 10:24:53,164 - INFO - Answer: ECHO Payment Methods include SimplicityÂ® EPC, ECHO Brand name "QuicRemit", Payer Specific Virtual Card, Electronic Funds Transfer (EFT or ACH), and Virtual Card Payments. ECHO issues payments to providers by EFT, virtual credit card, and paper draft. The method of payment used is based on factors such as TPA Enrollment, Provider Enrollment, Provider Opt-out (Virtual Card), Virtual Card Exceptions, and each payment flows through the ECHO payment hierarchy to determine the appropriate payment. ECHO issues Virtual Card Payments by mail or fax. The provider receives the card, sends a transmission of credit card transactions (batch) to the merchant acquirer/bank, which processes the payment (settlement). The ECHO Card Issuer validates if the card is valid and funds are available (Authorizes or declines the transaction).
