2025-07-31 18:56:47,508 - INFO - Answer: 1. Virtual Card Payment: A payment method that allows users to make online payments using digital cards, which are essentially unique credit or debit card numbers used for a single transaction. These digital cards can be generated and used without the need for physically presenting the physical card.

2. One-time use virtual card: A term referring to a virtual card that is only valid for one transaction. The card number is not stored anywhere and expires after the transaction has been completed, providing an additional layer of security.

3. Digital representation of a physical credit or debit card: A term describing the electronic version of a physical credit or debit card used for online transactions. This digital card functions similarly to its physical counterpart but does not require the user to physically present the card during the transaction.
