2025-07-31 19:23:41,846 - INFO - Support Answer: 1. Error: 00159 Expiring Drafts Report Includes Cleared Items
     - Reason: Failure to correctly purge faulty claims.
     - Resolution: Claims purged from /97 for Guardian during mid-late 2020 failed to purge from History, leading to both File1 and File 2 having entries for the same payments in table CheckRegister. The second set of claims was due to a known issue with form code setting sp in epp selection process, which led to a claim getting duplicated, one with the correct data which cleared, and one with faulty data which never went anywhere.

  2. Error: Certain clients have Users assigned to their SOFT access. Any time a change is made in SOFT for that client a notification is sent to the master user and they have to approve or deny the changes (address updates, voids/reissues etc) To see if a client has a Master User set up check tpa table in the client database: If these columns are populated then the client uses Master Users.
     - Reason: SOFT Master User Set up needed
     - Resolution: To make a user a master user you have to add their login id to the MasterUserLoginId column and their email address to the MasterUserEmailAddress column in the tpa table in the client database. You can use the following update statement to insert the login is and emailaddress into the tpa table, just update the client database name and the variables

  3. Error: This error occurs on the production side when attempting to open the Production Cycle application.  The error message refers to a live draft that is not in a state that will allow the production cycle app to lock the tables.
     - Reason: Production Control Reissue Live Draft Error
     - Resolution: We need to identify the check that is causing the block. To do this we query the tmp Reissued Drafts table and look for any checks with an error_flag set to 1. Take the echeck and find that draft in tableorheader. Look for the form_code, also verify the check is in nineteendb as well. Mark down the EPPID, you will need that later. We next take the echecknumber and use it to get the presentmentbatchid from table presentmentdetail to find out who approved the reissue (this is for documentation purposes and not germane to the solution). Next we are going to resolve the issue by changing the status of the EPPID we wrote down earlier associates with the echecknumber to a 3. This change will allow the Production Control app to skip over this check and lock the table for production. UPDATE payorheadertable for the EPPID. Do the same to nineteendb Finally email the finance team to let them know what happened regarding the failed reissue of the draft. In this instance a Vpay draft was cleared via banking program but should not have been.

  4. Error: OSS receives an error message in reference code . The rep is unable to access certain pages in SOFT because a payment record has not been created. The ask is to create a payment record for the new client
     - Reason: SOFT set up needed
     - Resolution: Run the query, making sure to put the name of the database you want to use. This query will insert a dummy record into the Approval cycle table and allow OSS and CS to enter all the pages in SOFT.
